A vintage-style technical illustration showing an intricate clockwork mechanism with multiple interconnected gears of varying sizes, where some gears are clearly original brass-colored components while others are sleek chrome replacement parts seamlessly integrated into the system. The composition shows a cross-section view of this hybrid mechanical assembly, with delicate watch-making tools like tiny screwdrivers and tweezers resting nearby on a worn wooden workbench. Warm amber lighting from an old desk lamp casts dramatic shadows across the scene, highlighting the contrast between original and customized parts. The aesthetic evokes 1950s technical manuals with subtle sepia tones and fine crosshatching details in the background.
